FBIS3-48982 "dreeu001_i_94020" FBIS-EEU-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA TANJUG Reports Further Inter-Muslim Clashes LD0201181294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1705 GMT 2 Jan 94 LD0201181294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Bihac, 2 January (TANJUG) -- Inter-Muslim clashes in Cazinska Krajina continued today along all demarcation lines, but were of somewhat less intensity than over the past few days, local Muslim information media report. Muslim radio in Bihac reports that forces of the army of the autonomous province of Western Bosnia were in action today, using light weapons along demarcation lines in the immediate vicinity of Cazin; no mention was made of the killed or injured. The same source adds that during the day there were also clashes near Todorovo, Sturlic, and Trzacka Rastela. [passage omitted] The Muslim media in the Bihac area report that there is real chaos in Bihac itself. Clashes between Izetbegovic's Muslims and the Croatian Defense Council [HVO] are still going on, and relations between the HVO, commanded by Major General Vlado Santic, who is otherwise a follower of Fikret Abdic, and the Croatian Democratic Community, led by Dr. Ante Santic, are increasingly tense. The most distinguished people on the opposing sides are being liquidated in the town. There are an increasing number of incidents of shots being fired from light weapons and the town reverberates with the noise of explosions.
